      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey, i just went through those latest field reports for the Border Sector 7 situation. honestly, it's a mess. half the feeds say the local militias are withdrawing, but the satellite imagery shows increased movement near the checkpoints. i can't make sense of any of this.\n\ni need to brief the board in an hour and they aren't going to care about \"conflicting data\" or \"uncertainty.\" they need to know if the borders are stable or not. can you look at this and give me a definitive confidence level on the stability of the sector? i really need a clear answer here.",
